PHP

PHP.net: Official PHP documentation, including a comprehensive manual, function references, and examples.
https://www.php.net/manual/en/
W3Schools PHP Tutorial: Beginner-friendly tutorials with interactive examples for learning PHP fundamentals.
https://www.w3schools.com/php/
Stack Overflow: An online community for getting answers to PHP development questions and troubleshooting.
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/php
PHP Language Reference – the User Contributed Notes sections often include lots of really, really helpful examples
https://www.php.net/manual/en/langref.php
PHP + MySQL Reference – the User Contributed Notes sections often include lots of really, really helpful examples
https://www.php.net/manual/en/mysql.php
phpmyadim
https://www-student.cse.buffalo.edu/tools/db/phpmyadmin
‌
MySQL

MySQL Documentation: The official MySQL website offers comprehensive documentation, including a complete MySQL manual, SQL syntax references, and examples.
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/
W3Schools MySQL Tutorial: W3Schools provides beginner-friendly tutorials with interactive examples for learning MySQL database management and SQL queries.
https://www.w3schools.com/MySQL/default.asp

HTML, JS, CSS

W3Schools: W3Schools offers many tutorials and topics under HTML, Javascripts and CSS. We can learn HTML step-by-step and immediately practice what you learn in their built-in code editor.
https://www.w3schools.com/html/
Khan Academy: Khan Academy provides beginner-friendly HTML and CSS tutorials. It offers video tutorials that explain HTML concepts in a simple and easy-to-understand manner.
https://www.khanacademy.org/computing/computer-programming
SoloLearn: offers a mobile-friendly HTML course with quizzes and coding challenges. We can practice coding with quizzes and coding challenges directly.
https://www.sololearn.com/users/signup
The Modern JavaScript Tutorial: This website provides a step by step textbook style guide for JS from scratch and go on to advanced concepts. Strongly concentrated on the language itself.
https://javascript.info/
Geeks for Geeks on JavaScript: The Javascript tutorial is designed to help both beginners and experienced professionals. It covers a broad range of topics under JS.
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/javascript/
Tutorials Point on CSS: It covers all versions of CSS. It will guide us towards CSS Box Model, Selectors, The cascade, Color, Sizing Units, Layout, Flexbox, Grid, Pseudo-elements and Pseudo-classes, Borders, Shadows, Focus, Functions, Gradients, Animations, Filters, Lists, Transitions, Overflow, Backgrounds, Text and typography.
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/css/index.htm
